parameter 6: From January 23rd, 2001 to April 17th, 2001 the German TV station Arbeitsgemeinschaft der öffentlich-rechtlichen Rundfunkanstalten der Bundesrepublik Deutschland (ARD) released the first season of the series. parameter 7: In 2005 a new version of the series was released. All episodes were edited new (25 episodes) and got a new title song. The series became called "Plötzlich erwachsen!".

parameter 9: In the first season, there was one opening credit sequence made up entirely of location footage shot on tape in Chicago and a slightly different recording of the theme song. This was used for three weeks, then replaced with another opening sequence mixing live-action footage and an animated sequence. This lasted a few weeks and was replaced by yet another sequence mixing the location footage shot in Chicago and clips from episodes, ending with the tail end of the animated sequence being watched by the lead characters on TV. This third opening sequence is on all first season episodes in syndication in the United States, but the DVD versions have the appropriate sequences reinstated depending on the episode.

parameter 13: A "director's cut" version aired 7/20/2012, and is included with the Season 2 DVD.
